=== Outside-precinct shrines ===
Sasu Shinmeigu and Kashinoki Inari, once merged in 1911, were re-enshrined at their former locations in 1942.<ref name="guide"/>

* Sasu Shinmeigu (next to Gion-ji)
: Deity: {{ill|lt=Amaterasu|Q455602|qid=Q455602|lt=Amaterasu Omikami|1=Amaterasu}}
: Festival: December 13

* Kashinoki Inari (southwest corner of Koka Gakuen grounds)
: Deity: {{ill|qid=Q3080728|lt=Ukanomitama|Q3080728|qid=Q3080728|qid=Q3080728|lt=Ukanomitama-no-Mikoto|1=Ukanomitama}}
: Festival: Hatsuuma day in February

=== Annual events ===
* Monthly festival (13th of each month except January and October)
* New Year's Day festival (January 1)
* Inari Hatsuuma festival (first horse day of February)
* Kohaku Shrine grand festival (first Sunday of October)
* Shinmeigu grand festival (December 13)
* Niiname-sai (December 13)

=== Access ===
* From JR Mitaka Station, Keio Bus for Chofu Station; get off at "Sasu," about 5 minutes on foot.
* From Keio Chofu Station, Keio Bus for Mitaka Station; get off at "Sasu," about 5 minutes on foot.
* Chofu City minibuses also stop at "Kohaku Shrine."

